genresAdvancedInfo.name: yorkshire folk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Yorkshire folk music is a traditional genre that originated in the North of England. It is characterized by its use of acoustic instruments such as the guitar, fiddle and accordion, and its focus on storytelling through song. The lyrics often draw on local history and folklore, and the music has a strong sense of community and identity.
